<section class="hero is-small is-dark">
	<div class="container">
		<br><h2 class="title">FAQ</h2>
		<div class="card">
		  <header class="card-header">
		    <p class="card-header-title">
		      Is this form of data collection legal?
		    </p>
		  </header>
		  <div class="card-content">
		    <div class="content">
		      Packet sniffing in the United States is legal for many usecases. However, using the technology to monitor user communications can be considered unwarranted wiretapping. Constellation's tools only read the headers of a particular type of packet with no user data. This is completely legal and protects the privacy of your customers. 
		    </div>
		  </div>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
		  <header class="card-header">
		    <p class="card-header-title">
		      Can I use the internet on my computer while using Observatory?
		    </p>
		  </header>
		  <div class="card-content">
		    <div class="content">
		      In order to work properly, Observatory has to control your WiFi radio in your computer and cannot share that with your normal internet habbits. However, when you purchase Singularity, we'll ship you a USB WiFi dongle that Observatory can use exclusively. That way you can still browse the internet while Observatory runs.  
		    </div>
		  </div>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
		  <header class="card-header">
		    <p class="card-header-title">
		      Do you sell data to 3rd parties?
		    </p>
		  </header>
		  <div class="card-content">
		    <div class="content">
		      No, Constellation is focused on providing data and analytics to business owners, not third parties. We do not attempt to identify your customers. Your data is only accessible by you and anyone you give access to.   
		    </div>
		  </div>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
		  <header class="card-header">
		    <p class="card-header-title">
		      I have Observatory running at multiple locations? How can I join that data?
		    </p>
		  </header>
		  <div class="card-content">
		    <div class="content">
		      When you purchase Singularity, you can configure your Observatory instances to push all their data to Singularity. From the Singularity web app, you can slice and dice the data all at once.  
		    </div>
		  </div>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
		  <header class="card-header">
		    <p class="card-header-title">
		      What is Open Source and what does it mean for Observatory?
		    </p>
		  </header>
		  <div class="card-content">
		    <div class="content">
		      Observatory is fully Open Source. Meaning you, or anyone, can inspect the code and ensure that security, privacy and accuracy is at the level we claim. Even if Constellation goes out of business, that code will always be available so that you'll never be cut off from your data.
		    </div>
		  </div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
